You need to implement:

## 1. LEVEL MODIFIER SYSTEM

Add a wave modifier concept. Each wave can have an optional modifier that changes rules.

Add to game.js near state variables:
```javascript
let waveModifier = null; // current active modifier: null, 'sniperAlley', 'swarm', 'gauntlet', 'fog', 'harvestMoon', 'doubleTrouble'
let waveModifierData = {}; // per-modifier runtime data
```

Add a function that determines the modifier for a wave:
```javascript
function getWaveModifier(lv) {
  if (isBossWave(lv)) return null; // boss waves have no modifier
  // Assign modifiers to specific waves (cycling pattern)
  // Sniper Alley: waves 7, 12, 17, 22, 27...
  // The Swarm: waves 8, 16, 24, 32...
  // The Gauntlet: waves 25, 50, 75... (every 25th)
  // Fog Bank: waves 4, 9, 14, 19... (reserved for future)
  // Harvest Moon: waves 3, 8, 13, 18... (reserved for future)

  if (lv % 25 === 0 && lv >= 25) return 'gauntlet';
  if (lv >= 7 && (lv - 7) % 5 === 0 && !isBossWave(lv)) return 'sniperAlley';
  if (lv >= 8 && (lv - 8) % 8 === 0 && !isBossWave(lv)) return 'swarm';
  return null;
}
```

In startLevel(), set the modifier:
```javascript
waveModifier = getWaveModifier(level);
waveModifierData = {};
```

Add modifier-specific level banner text. In the level banner section of startLevel():
```javascript
if (waveModifier === 'sniperAlley') {
  levelBannerSubtitle = levelBannerSubtitle ? levelBannerSubtitle + ' - SNIPER ALLEY' : 'SNIPER ALLEY';
}
if (waveModifier === 'swarm') {
  levelBannerSubtitle = levelBannerSubtitle ? levelBannerSubtitle + ' - THE SWARM' : 'THE SWARM';
}
if (waveModifier === 'gauntlet') {
  levelBannerSubtitle = 'THE GAUNTLET';
}
```

